@node "WHATIS" "WhAT Is It?"
·[ What Is It? ]·

Chaos Scan consists of 2 doors:  FSCAN and NSCAN, that replace the internal
DayDream  F and N commands..  I coded Chaos Scan because I didn't like very
much  the  look  of  the  original  file  listing functions of DayDream and
moreover because I wanted a fast #file number tagging routine and a reverse
scanning function..

So  here it is..  Chaos Scan is fast, has a nice ANSI design, it's reliable
and, last but not least, it features a smart ANSI scroll..

 ** THIS DOOR HAS BEEN CODED FOLLOWING THE OFFICIAL DAYDREAM DEVELOPER   ** 
 ** DOCUMENTATION AND IT'S ABLE TO HANDLE A LOSS OF CARRIER IN THE RIGHT ** 
 ** WAY, WITHOUT LOCKING THE SYSTEM AS OTHER DOORS DO..                  **
@endnode

@node "USAGE" "UsAgE"
·[ UsAGe ]·

[ N ] COMMAND

This is the syntax:  N DATE DIRECTORY 

DATE can be entered in various formats    dd-mm-yy : scan from specified date
                                               -dd : scan from #dd days ago
                                                 S : scan from last call
                                                 T : scan today's uploads
                                                 E : scan from top of dir

DIRECTORY can be a valid directory number or U for upload directory.

[ F ] COMMAND

This is the syntax: F R DIRECTORY

The switch R enables the REVERSE SCAN mode, useful to see recent uploads.

DIRECTORY can be a valid directory number or U for upload directory.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

cHAOS  sCAN  checks the user flag - CLS's in filelists - and if it's set to ON
enters the CLS SCAN MODE..

Chaos  Scan displays a prompt every time the list reaches the bottom of the
screen.   Here you can (Y) resume the scanning, (N) abort it, (T) tag files for
downloading,  (?) read the about scroll (DO IT!!).  

Some  words for the tag routine that allows you to select files by name, by the
unique  number  associated  to  each file AND ALSO BY BOTH AT THE SAME TIME. I
mean  that  at the tag prompt you can enter "1 2 3", "FOOBAR.LHA PIPPO.DMS" but
also "FOOBAR.LHA 3 4 PIPPO.LHA".  Innovative, isn't it?


From  V1.17  of DayDream, the function I used to break the about scroll has
been  modified  and  now  the  user is no longer able to stop the scroll by
pressing a key.  I hope to find a new solution soon, in the meanwhile enjoy
reading the entire text.. `)
@endnode

@node "INSTALL" "InStAllATiON"
·[ InsTALLaTION ]·

Not  so  Hard,  I  guess..   Just  copy  SCAN.X  and  NSCAN.X in your DOORS
directory,  then  put  2  entries  for  them into your DAYDREAM.CFG and say
goodbye to the old F and N commands..


Ie. If you keep your doors in DOORS: you should add this to your DAYDREAM.CFG

 + 
 DOOR_COMMAND.. N 
 DOOR_TYPE..... 1 
 DOOR_SECURITY. 5 
 DOOR_EXECUTE.. Doors:NSCAN.X %N 
 + 
 DOOR_COMMAND.. F 
 DOOR_TYPE..... 1 
 DOOR_SECURITY. 5
 DOOR_EXECUTE.. Doors:SCAN.X %N 
 +

Before  asking  for  the dir number to scan, cHAOS sCAN, looks for a banner
file  and  if  one  is found it will be showed.  This is the sequence cHAOS
sCAN follows to looks for the banner.

DayDream:CONFS/MODS/Display/Iso/filecatalogs.255.GFX
DayDream:CONFS/MODS/Display/Iso/filecatalogs.GFX
DayDream:Display/Iso/filecatalogs.255.GFX
DayDream:Display/Iso/filecatalogs.GFX

Where "Daydream:CONFS/MODS/" is the conference path, "iso" is the selected
display mode and "255" is the user access level.

oKEE?
@endnode

